events.name: Hack Night with GDG
events.description:
Hello All,

Get your laptop and join us for a Hack Night by Google Developer Group, Houston in partnership with Byte Academy.

We'll be doing a quick "standup" for intros at 6:00 pm then get to programming right after. Developers, designers, and others of all levels are welcome. Bring a project and work solo or find a pair at standup.

GDG and Instructors from the Byte Academy team will be there to help provide guidance. We'll have refreshments on hand too!

*Directions: At WeWork Galleria Office Tower 1 take the escalator to the third floor then the elevator to the 21st Floor
events.how_to_find_us: At WeWork Galleria Office Tower 1 take the escalator to the third floor then the elevator to the 21st Floor

events.name: GDG DevFest Houston 2019
events.description:
DevFest Houston is a single-day, single-track, inclusive conference for all developers. GDG Houston and Women Techmakers Houston invite you to join us on Saturday, September 28, 2019 at CUBIO Innovation Center in Houston for our first annual DevFest!
Please visit https://devfesthouston.com/ for more details and register.

Ticket grants access to breakfast, all conference sessions, hands-on code labs and lunch, a t-shirt, entry to giveaways, and more!

NOTE: RSVPs on meetup are not sufficient for admission. Please RSVP and register at https://devfesthouston.com/ to reserve your ticket.

Sponsors:
Google, ChaiOne, CUBIO, JetBrains, Byte Academy, O'Reilly.

Partner Organizations:
Women Who Code, Houston Flutter Group, Houston PyLadies.
events.how_to_find_us: Find us on 2nd floor. You'll see a glass window facing the elevators and CUBIO logo. Parking in front is free, and there is additional free visitor parking at the back of the building.  If full, park on the small side street to "Sun Behavior Houston"

events.name: ML Cloud Study Jam Houston
events.description:
Event is free but only for CONFIRMED applicants. Please REGISTER at https://bit.ly/gdghou-studyjam for consideration. Confirmations will be sent on rolling basis. **RSVPs on meetup are NOT sufficient for admission.**
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Get official Google training, a $55 value, free of charge.

Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud technologies as a team. Join us for our upcoming Cloud Study Jam and get hands-on experience with Machine Learning.

After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home. Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Agenda of the Event:
09:00 AM - Check-in, Breakfast and Networking
10:00 AM - Welcome and Intro to ML
10:30 AM - Get free access to Qwiklabs
11:00 AM - Lab 1: AI Platform: Qwik Start
12:00 PM - Lab 2: Google Cloud Speech API: Qwik Start
01:00 PM - Lunch/Break(Lunch is provided:)
02:00 PM - Lab 3: Cloud Natural Language API: Qwik Start
03:00 PM - Lab 4: Entity and Sentiment Analysis with Natural Language API
04:00 PM - Lab 5: Speech to Text Transcription with the Cloud Speech API
04:45 PM - Celebration and Prize announcements

*Thanks to our Local Sponsors*
Digital Crafts at The Cannon
Serverless Solutions LLC
events.how_to_find_us: Please drive through main entrance off of Brittmoore & continue following the driveway to the left of the building. From there, please park in any open parking spot & enter the building through North entrance, continue down the hallway to front desk.

upcoming.name: Build Actions for the Google Assistant
upcoming.description:
We wanted to start this year with more engaging events and tech-talks for the community and our first event of this year is "Build Actions for the Google Assistant".

Actions on Google is a developer platform that lets you create software to extend the functionality of the Google Assistant, Google's virtual personal assistant, across more than 1 billion devices, including smart speakers, phones, cars, TVs, headphones, and more.

You do not need to have any prior experience with the platform to follow this codelab. This is a HANDS-ON event.

Food and Drinks are provided.
-----------------------------------------------
What to bring to the event:
Laptop
Laptop charger
The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, use Firefox or Chrome.
Looking forward to seeing you at the event!
-----------------------------------------------
Agenda:
6:00 PM - 6:45 PM Check-in/Networking/Food
6:45 PM - 7:45 PM CodeLabs
7:45 PM - 8:00 PM Break
8:00 PM - 8:30 PM Resources and Discussion
-----------------------------------------------
*Thanks Flatiron School for sponsoring this event !!*

Parking:
Street/meter parking is free after 6 PM. There are meters available along Capitol Street, Texas Street, and Rusk Street.
Nearby available garages include Walker @ Main and 803 Fannin.
upcoming.how_to_find_us: Flatiron School is located inside the WeWork the Jones Building on the 4th Floor located at 708 Main Street, Houston, TX 77002. The building is located across from BirdDog Saint and right next to Shake Shack.

upcoming.name: International Women's Day - IWD Houston 2020
upcoming.description:
Event is FREE but only for CONFIRMED applicants.
Please REGISTER at https://bit.ly/wtmhou-iwd2020 for consideration. Confirmations will be sent on rolling basis.
**RSVPs on meetup are NOT sufficient for admission.**
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

International Women’s Day (IWD) celebrations range from general respect and appreciation toward women to a celebration of women’s economic, political, and social achievements.

This International Women's Day, we’re inviting our community to share their superpowers - those special qualities that make you shine. Whether you’re creating space for more voices to be heard or you’re working to secure funding as an entrepreneur, you’re a superhero in our book. Together let’s celebrate the super-women in our lives. Together let’s create a new narrative for our industry.
#TogetherWeRise #WTM #IWD
